=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Tour_of_UGens_ex33 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 501 Hz, featuring instant attack and dynamic envelope, with evolving spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: evolving
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 501.0658
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.2455
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8930
  pitch_clarity: 16.0159
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -3.6085
  resonance_freq: 495.2637

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Tour of UGens Example 33
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Tour_of_UGens.html
// Tags: Tour_of_UGens, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 33 ---
// a signal with impulse noise.
{ Saw.ar(500, 0.1) + Dust2.ar(100, 0.9) }.play;
// after applying median filter
{ Median.ar(3, Saw.ar(500, 0.1) + Dust2.ar(100, 0.9)) }.play;

// a signal with impulse noise.
{ Saw.ar(500, 0.1) + Dust2.ar(100, 0.9) }.play;
// after applying slew rate limiter
{ Slew.ar(Saw.ar(500, 0.1) + Dust2.ar(100, 0.9),1000,1000) }.play;
